"Welcome endings and new beginning " it would whisper to me. The light starts to soften around me as Elohim invites me into the twilight of the year.
•
If you were to place 365 days into 24 hrs, September would be that magic hour. That time before the darkness settles closely to the hills. 
For us westerners, twilight is just the end of a day.
For Jews, it is the new day- sabbath's and holy days start as the last twinkling, the sun drifts behind the horizon and rest comes. 
•
Rosh Hashanah ( or Jewish New Year) is on the first day of the Hebrew month Tishrei. Which almost always happens to be in September. A new beginning for Jews is always at twilight. 
•
A time to reflect on the day, to settle into rest, to simple be. The golden hours , High Holy Days, whatever you call it, however you live your life- I hope you seek out rest this months.
Let September be a month of sanctity for you- of going back to your true loves in this life. Let Septembers golden hour set aflame a fervent reverence for slowing down life, getting in touch with nature and God. With yourself.
•
Let September 2020, amidst tragedies and all those things that anger you right now, let it spark new life in you!
Embrace the twilight of 2020 and settle into a sanctuary of peace.
.
